    "As a function of the signal efficiency, the ROC curve is a step-wise, monotonically increasing function.",
    "Its integral can be estimated by the sum of bins with width 1/N gen, the inverse size of the generated dataset.",
    "The height of each rectangle is the fraction of weights in the true, or training dataset, which are larger than a given w cut, normalized to N true.",
    "The AUC is then given by the sum, AUC = 1 N gen N true w i ∈gen |{w|w ∈ true and w > w i }|,where |{S}| denotes the cardinality of the set S. Therefore, by focusing on the weight distribution of the classifier, we are not missing any information otherwise contained in the AUC.In this paper we will use three standard LHC applications of generative models to develop a common strategy to quantify the performance of the networks.",
